Granite Hacarmel Advances Most in a Week on Azrieli Sale Report

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-10-05T08:58:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/granite-hacarmel-advances-most-in-a-week-on-azrieli-sale-report.html
Granite Hacarmel Investments Ltd. (GRNT) 
increased the most in a week after Calcalist reported that
 Azrieli Group (AZRG)  Ltd. may sell the marketer of petroleum and
automobile products.  Granite Hacarmel shares climbed 7.6 percent, the biggest
intraday gain since Sept. 27, to 5.649 shekels at 10:27 a.m. in
Tel Aviv. Azrieli shares increased 1.3 percent to 86.25 shekels.  “A number of people have approached us for the acquisition
of Granite,” Azrieli Group said in a statement read by
telephone. Kanit Hashalom, a subsidiary of Azrieli, owns 60.68
percent of Granite, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  